> StorageTest

@maektwain see https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FINERACT-828 about that one (search JIRA!), do you want to see if you can help to fix that one, in a separate PR? The (latest build of this) PR doesn't fail because of that test though, but due to https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FINERACT-899... do you know how we could fix that?

Perhaps more importantly than those test failure, this PR has merge conflicts now, and a weird Commit history... 44 commits, of which many which are already on `develop` now - I think something went wrong during your `git rebase`.. do you want to update this to have 1 clean commit only?

@maektwain  the (latest build of this) PR now fails due to https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FINERACT-899... do you know how we could fix that? A contribution from you for that would be really really really welcome!

This PR also has a weird Commit history... 12 commits, of which many which are already on develop now - I think something went wrong during your git rebase.. do you want to update this to have 1 clean commit only?

Once there is a clean diff, it will be easier to understand and review what this proposes. Would this cause EVERY git commit locally to run full integration tests? I'm not entirely sure yet if that is not too much. At least me I relatively often make small changes, and would want to be able to commit them without having to run full integration tests locally. I'm assuming that the problem you are trying to solve is the failing PRs on GitHub. But the reason for that, IMHO, isn't really that people don't run tests locally - I think they (mostly) do. What's really hurting us is are all the flaky test issues linked from https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FINERACT-850. If you really want to help and have an impact, we would love help to sort that out...

@xurror can you locally run and fix `./gradlew rat` ? Some license header is missing.

BTW this has nothing to do with [FINERACT-905](https://jira.apache.org/jira/browse/FINERACT-905), confusion.

PS please ignore the failed Build - Summary, and only look at Travis (see [FINERACT-907](https://jira.apache.org/jira/browse/FINERACT-907)).

@awasum OK for you to also merge this one - a 3rd failing IT? @nikpawar89 any objections?

as per (new) #782 policy

for FINERACT-899
